Business Brief -- Student Loan Marketing:
   Fourth-Quarter Profit Rose
   17% on Improving Yields
If Treasury bill rates remain at today's levels throughout
1992, said Lawrence A. Hough, president and chief executive
officer, then Sallie Mae's per-share earnings growth will
keep exceeding its 15% long-term annual growth target.
   Sallie Mae bought $1.5 billion in student loans in the
fourth quarter, bringing its loan portfolio to $22.07
billion, up 15% from $19.24 billion at the end of 1990.
Assets grew to $45.32 billion from $42.12 billion.